Barcelona Ties Sevilla, Ronaldo’s Hat Trick Leads Madrid in Spanish Soccer

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-10-22T22:03:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-22/barcelona-ties-as-messi-misses-penalty-ronaldo-scores-hat-trick.html
Javier Varas stopped  Lionel Messi ’s
penalty kick in stoppage time as Sevilla tied Barcelona 0-0 in
Spanish soccer’s Primera Liga.  Cristiano Ronaldo scored a hat trick as Real Madrid beat
Malaga 4-0 to move to the top of the standings. Real leads
Barcelona by one point with Levante two points behind and
Sevilla three points back.  Monpellier won 3-1 at Caen to tie PSG at the top of
France’s Ligue One, while Andrea Caracciolo’s goal in the 85th
minute gave Genoa a 2-2 tie at first-place Juventus in Italy’s
Serie A.  Defending champion Dortmund routed Cologne 5-0 to move
within three points of  Bayern Munich  in the German Bundesliga.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  